# Environment Variables

To run the learning service with Gemini API integration, you need to set the following environment variables:

## Required Variables

- `GEMINI_API_KEY`: Your Google Gemini API key
  - Get one from [Google AI Studio](https://aistudio.google.com/)
  - Make sure to enable the Gemini API in your Google Cloud project

## Optional Variables

- `GEMINI_MODEL_NAME`: The Gemini model to use (default: gemini-1.5-pro-latest)
- `GEMINI_API_TIMEOUT`: Timeout for API requests in seconds (default: 30)
- `GEMINI_SAFETY_THRESHOLD`: Safety threshold for content filtering (default: BLOCK_MEDIUM_AND_ABOVE)
- `ENV_FILE`: Path to environment file to load (default: .env)
- `GOOGLE_CLOUD_PROJECT`: Your Google Cloud Project ID (required for BigQuery)
- `BIGQUERY_DATASET_ID`: BigQuery dataset ID (default: learning_analytics)
- `GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS`: Path to service account key file (required for BigQuery authentication)

## Example .env file

```
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_actual_api_key_here
GEMINI_MODEL_NAME=gemini-1.5-pro-latest
GEMINI_API_TIMEOUT=30
GOOGLE_CLOUD_PROJECT=your-google-cloud-project-id
BIGQUERY_DATASET_ID=learning_analytics
GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS=/path/to/your/service-account-key.json
```

## Development Environment

For development, you can use the `.env.development` file which contains placeholder values:

```
ENV_FILE=.env.development
```

This will load the development environment variables, which include a placeholder for the API key. The application will automatically fall back to mock data if the API key is not set or is invalid.